1
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:05,797
- Karuizawa, Nagano Prefecture, Japan.

2
00:00:14,165 --> 00:00:17,130
Yes! Strike!

3
00:00:17,213 --> 00:00:20,136
Nice one, Ran.
Not bad at all.

4
00:00:20,219 --> 00:00:23,350
Tennis was a bust,
but bowling's fun too.

5
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,398
We missed out on
miniskirt tennis girls,

6
00:00:26,481 --> 00:00:29,487
and there's one old man
drowning his sorrows over it.

7
00:00:30,406 --> 00:00:32,910
Come on, you're up next, Conan-kun.
Okay.

8
00:00:32,995 --> 00:00:35,875
Go for it, Conan-kun.
Don't choke, squirt.

9
00:00:36,793 --> 00:00:40,718
So who is it, anyway...
the person you wanted me to meet?

10
00:00:40,801 --> 00:00:44,309
Oh, that would be the person who waited

11
00:00:44,392 --> 00:00:46,104
four hours on a tennis court
in the pouring rain.

12
00:00:46,188 --> 00:00:49,652
They're changing out of their wet clothes,
should be here any minute.

13
00:00:49,736 --> 00:00:52,325
Quit dragging it out
and just tell me.

14
00:00:52,408 --> 00:00:55,331
I rode my bike all the way
here through this rain.

15
00:00:56,541 --> 00:00:57,543
Huh?

16
00:01:00,341 --> 00:01:01,593
What's your problem?

17
00:01:04,057 --> 00:01:06,561
You want to take me on?

18
00:01:07,522 --> 00:01:09,609
Hyah! Hah!

19
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:13,242
Jeet Kune Do.

20
00:01:13,325 --> 00:01:14,911
He dodged it.

21
00:01:22,677 --> 00:01:23,804
Tch...

22
00:01:24,305 --> 00:01:27,478
Interesting. I'll pound you into the ground.

23
00:01:31,903 --> 00:01:33,657
Blazing sun,
beating the heat,

24
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:35,411
a slick and stylish
deduction show.

25
00:01:35,494 --> 00:01:39,669
The man Sonoko adores arrives,
a showdown brews at the bowling alley.

26
00:01:39,752 --> 00:01:41,131
There's only one truth.

27
00:01:41,214 --> 00:01:42,968
Looks like a kid,
mind of an adult.

28
00:01:43,051 --> 00:01:45,472
His name... Detective Conan!

29
00:01:47,694 --> 00:01:53,079
♪~

30
00:03:21,215 --> 00:03:27,227
~♪

31
00:03:29,194 --> 00:03:33,294
"Makoto Kyogoku, A Suspect? (Part 1)"

32
00:03:38,081 --> 00:03:41,087
Interesting. I'll pound you into the ground.

33
00:03:41,171 --> 00:03:43,676
No, wait, Sera-san!
Huh?

34
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:47,350
That's him. The person Sonoko
wanted you to meet.

35
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:48,435
Huh?

36
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:53,404
Ahem. This is my boyfriend,
Makoto Kyogoku-san.

37
00:03:53,487 --> 00:03:56,201
And this is my classmate,
Masumi Sera-san.

38
00:03:56,285 --> 00:03:58,956
Oh... you're a woman?

39
00:03:59,749 --> 00:04:04,676
My apologies. I assumed you were
some lout harassing Sonoko-san.

40
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:06,430
Don't worry about it.

41
00:04:06,513 --> 00:04:09,394
Getting mistaken for a guy
happens to me all the time.

42
00:04:09,728 --> 00:04:12,525
Honestly, Sonoko, why didn't
you stop them sooner?

43
00:04:12,608 --> 00:04:17,327
But I wanted to see
the two of them fight!

44
00:04:17,410 --> 00:04:20,040
Good grief. What if someone got hurt?
- Kyogoku-san, here. Your glasses.
45
00:04:20,124 --> 00:04:20,666
Kyogoku-san, here.  Your glasses.

45
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:22,420
Heh heh, my apologies. Ah, much obliged.

46
00:04:22,503 --> 00:04:23,922
Come now, it's fine.

47
00:04:24,466 --> 00:04:27,388
I wouldn't have minded
sparring with him a bit longer.

48
00:04:27,472 --> 00:04:28,807
Honestly.

49
00:04:28,891 --> 00:04:31,438
Who taught you Jeet Kune Do?

50
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:36,740
My brother. Though he was about
three times stronger than me.

51
00:04:36,823 --> 00:04:38,285
B-but...

52
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:41,792
didn't you say
your brother passed away?

53
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:44,798
Yeah, that's what I was told.
B-but...

54
00:04:45,383 --> 00:04:49,349
the other day, didn't you
call your brother on the phone?

55
00:04:49,682 --> 00:04:52,730
Oh, you heard that call?

56
00:04:53,607 --> 00:04:58,450
There's one more of us... my middle
brother, sharp as a tack.

57
00:04:58,826 --> 00:05:02,166
Unlike me and our late brother,
he takes after our dad,

58
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:04,170
so we don't look much alike.

59
00:05:04,671 --> 00:05:08,262
Seems he's in the middle of
some big job right now,

60
00:05:08,345 --> 00:05:11,143
won't tell me a thing
about where he is,

61
00:05:11,226 --> 00:05:15,192
but every so often I run my
deductions by him over call or text.

62
00:05:15,526 --> 00:05:17,655
That last case, my brother told me

63
00:05:17,738 --> 00:05:20,911
that my reasoning
was on shaky ground.

64
00:05:20,995 --> 00:05:25,129
But with you around,
maybe you'll set me straight if I'm wrong.

65
00:05:25,463 --> 00:05:28,635
Ah... not me, but
Shinichi-niichan, I mean.

66
00:05:28,719 --> 00:05:30,973
Hm? Heh heh.

67
00:05:31,766 --> 00:05:33,562
Don't tell me she...

68
00:05:33,645 --> 00:05:36,651
She knows I'm
Shinichi Kudo?

69
00:05:36,985 --> 00:05:38,238
(clears throat)

70
00:05:38,322 --> 00:05:40,117
By the way, Sonoko-san,

71
00:05:40,201 --> 00:05:43,499
did something go wrong
when you washed that outfit?

72
00:05:43,832 --> 00:05:47,005
Huh? Wrong? Oh...

73
00:05:47,507 --> 00:05:51,096
The collar's all stretched out
and your underwear is showing.

74
00:05:51,181 --> 00:05:54,312
Oh, n-no, this is what's
called off-the-shoulder.

75
00:05:54,395 --> 00:05:57,527
I'm showing it on purpose.
And this is a "show bra."

76
00:05:58,153 --> 00:05:59,697
A... show bra?

77
00:05:59,781 --> 00:06:03,372
You mean that undergarment
is meant to be shown?

78
00:06:03,872 --> 00:06:05,751
Th-that's right.

79
00:06:06,043 --> 00:06:09,968
Sonoko dressed up
just for you, Kyogoku-san.

80
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:15,604
More importantly, Kyogoku-san,
the back of your right hand is bleeding.

81
00:06:15,688 --> 00:06:18,235
Did that happen just now
when you sparred with Sera-san?

82
00:06:18,318 --> 00:06:21,366
No, this was outside earlier...
Um...

83
00:06:21,825 --> 00:06:23,954
I'm sorry about what happened earlier.
- Monna Michiko (30), junior high school mathematics teacher.

84
00:06:24,037 --> 00:06:25,874
Were you hurt?

85
00:06:25,958 --> 00:06:31,136
It's just a scratch on my end.
More importantly, how is he?

86
00:06:31,219 --> 00:06:36,688
He's fine. He brought it on himself.
My friend's carrying him to the car now.

87
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:37,898
Did something happen?

88
00:06:37,982 --> 00:06:41,489
When I stepped out earlier
to buy a change of clothes,

89
00:06:41,573 --> 00:06:45,414
this man's companion picked a fight
and caught one to the solar plexus.

90
00:06:45,497 --> 00:06:46,916
Ahaha.

91
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,503
Believe it or not,

92
00:06:48,587 --> 00:06:51,176
he's a middle school P.E. teacher.
- Masaki Sunami (29), junior high school science teacher.

93
00:06:51,259 --> 00:06:53,722
Normally he's a serious,
upstanding teacher,

94
00:06:53,805 --> 00:06:57,813
but Tanba-sensei here turns into
a different person when he drinks.

95
00:06:58,148 --> 00:07:00,527
So... how's he doing now?

96
00:07:00,611 --> 00:07:03,617
Passed out in the car.
In his sleep he was muttering,

97
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:07,082
"I'm gonna kill that bastard,"
or something like that.

98
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:08,293
(laughter)

99
00:07:08,710 --> 00:07:10,756
Anyway, what do we do now?

100
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:12,176
Let's see...

101
00:07:12,259 --> 00:07:15,557
He was supposed to teach me
how to bowl, but...

102
00:07:15,641 --> 00:07:17,728
Ladies.
Hm?

103
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:20,234
You seem to be
in quite a bind.

104
00:07:20,317 --> 00:07:21,611
(hiccup)

105
00:07:21,695 --> 00:07:26,036
If you'd like, allow yours truly
to give you a lesson or two.

106
00:07:27,456 --> 00:07:28,500
Uh...

107
00:07:31,088 --> 00:07:35,556
The hips, you see, the hips.
Bring your hips this way.

108
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:37,143
R-right.

109
00:07:37,226 --> 00:07:38,562
When you hold the ball,

110
00:07:38,645 --> 00:07:42,903
keep your pivot foot, the ball,
and your head all in a straight line.

111
00:07:42,987 --> 00:07:45,826
Okay.
Now, go ahead.

112
00:07:52,882 --> 00:07:54,343
Wow, amazing!

113
00:07:54,427 --> 00:07:56,473
That's it. Well done, well done.

114
00:07:57,683 --> 00:08:00,939
My, to be able to instruct
fine ladies such as yourselves,

115
00:08:01,023 --> 00:08:03,278
the honor goes back and forth,
much obliged-ums.

116
00:08:03,361 --> 00:08:04,572
Uh... right.

117
00:08:04,655 --> 00:08:08,037
Nyah ha ha ha!

118
00:08:08,121 --> 00:08:12,003
That old man's going to get
busted for harassment one of these days.

119
00:08:18,558 --> 00:08:21,314
Makoto-san, you can do it!

120
00:08:23,610 --> 00:08:25,823
(crowd murmuring)

121
00:08:27,993 --> 00:08:32,211
This guy's going to get busted
for property damage one of these days.

122
00:08:32,711 --> 00:08:34,507
J-just as I thought...

123
00:08:34,590 --> 00:08:37,888
fancy sports like this
aren't suited to me.

124
00:08:37,972 --> 00:08:39,725
I-I guess not.

125
00:08:40,435 --> 00:08:44,360
Besides, I only got back to the country
today, so I'm a bit jet-lagged.

126
00:08:44,443 --> 00:08:48,243
Oh, then why don't you take a nap
in my father's rental car?

127
00:08:48,743 --> 00:08:51,457
I've got the car keys
right here.

128
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:53,587
Then I'll take you up on that.

129
00:08:54,255 --> 00:08:56,509
(yawn)

130
00:08:56,593 --> 00:08:59,724
Aw, and this was supposed to
be a date with Makoto-san.

131
00:08:59,807 --> 00:09:03,063
Come on, it's fine.
We're getting dinner after this.

132
00:09:04,692 --> 00:09:06,779
Oh, Michiko, where are you going?

133
00:09:06,863 --> 00:09:09,075
I'm going to check
on Tanba-sensei.

134
00:09:09,577 --> 00:09:11,831
I'm a little worried.
I see.

135
00:09:11,915 --> 00:09:14,587
If he's sobered up,
I'll bring him back.

136
00:09:16,174 --> 00:09:17,885
Huh? He's gone?

137
00:09:18,303 --> 00:09:20,891
Tanba-sensei wasn't
in the car?

138
00:09:20,974 --> 00:09:24,398
No. It looks like he slipped out
and went off somewhere.

139
00:09:24,774 --> 00:09:27,821
Then why hasn't he come
to the bowling alley?

140
00:09:27,905 --> 00:09:31,871
Who knows? Maybe he's
sleeping it off behind a car or something.

141
00:09:31,955 --> 00:09:35,545
Don't joke like that. It's been
raining nonstop this whole time.

142
00:09:35,629 --> 00:09:37,633
W-well, that's true...

143
00:09:37,716 --> 00:09:39,887
If you're looking
for someone,

144
00:09:40,263 --> 00:09:42,601
leave it to me,
Kogoro Mouri.

145
00:09:42,685 --> 00:09:45,816
(hiccup)
Oh, my father's a detective.

146
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:49,740
K-Kogoro Mouri, you said?
The famous detective?

147
00:09:50,659 --> 00:09:54,250
Sensei.
Tanba-sensei.

148
00:09:54,917 --> 00:09:58,133
Are you in there?
Tanba-sensei.

149
00:09:58,550 --> 00:10:00,804
Tanba-sensei.

150
00:10:00,887 --> 00:10:03,184
No good. He's not
behind any of the cars.

151
00:10:03,727 --> 00:10:07,025
Maybe he's off drinking again
at some other place.

152
00:10:07,109 --> 00:10:10,449
Don't tell me he's
picking a fight with someone else...

153
00:10:10,532 --> 00:10:12,494
Then let's search the bars.

154
00:10:12,578 --> 00:10:13,663
Huh?
Yes.

155
00:10:14,373 --> 00:10:18,005
Hey, you lot help out too.
Check the places around here.

156
00:10:18,088 --> 00:10:20,177
Aw...
But how?

157
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:22,598
We don't even know
what the guy looks like.

158
00:10:23,349 --> 00:10:26,063
Here's a photo of him.
If you'd like,

159
00:10:26,147 --> 00:10:28,109
shall I send it to you?
Yeah.

160
00:10:28,485 --> 00:10:32,993
Hey, our rental car was
parked in this lot too, right?

161
00:10:33,077 --> 00:10:35,123
Yeah. Oh, Kyogoku-san.

162
00:10:35,207 --> 00:10:39,757
Right. But if anyone picks a fight with Makoto-san,

163
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:42,304
he'd fight back until they were beaten to a pulp...

164
00:10:42,387 --> 00:10:45,143
Well, I don't think I'd
beat anyone to a pulp.

165
00:11:02,302 --> 00:11:05,433
Damn it. He's
nowhere to be found.

166
00:11:05,517 --> 00:11:06,686
No luck here either.

167
00:11:07,061 --> 00:11:08,940
He hasn't gone back
to the car either.

168
00:11:09,023 --> 00:11:11,612
And his phone seems
to be switched off.

169
00:11:11,696 --> 00:11:12,990
Hm...

170
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:16,205
Where on earth
could he have gone?

171
00:11:16,289 --> 00:11:19,085
(water dripping)

172
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:22,176
What's that? What's
that sound?

173
00:11:24,012 --> 00:11:25,014
Hm.

174
00:11:26,225 --> 00:11:31,652
I checked under the cars too, but
he doesn't seem to be in this lot after all.

175
00:11:31,736 --> 00:11:34,533
Then maybe we should
file a missing person report...

176
00:11:34,617 --> 00:11:37,706
Ah! Kyaaa!

177
00:11:37,789 --> 00:11:38,791
Wh-what's wrong?

178
00:11:39,919 --> 00:11:42,257
Th-the restroom door
was unlocked,

179
00:11:42,341 --> 00:11:45,430
so I opened it, and...
inside there was...

180
00:12:03,338 --> 00:12:08,516
Petechiae in the palpebral conjunctiva.
Frothy fluid from the mouth.

181
00:12:09,017 --> 00:12:13,442
No swelling in the face,
no strangulation marks on the neck.

182
00:12:14,152 --> 00:12:15,447
Drowning, then.

183
00:12:16,239 --> 00:12:19,955
And no restraint marks
on the hands or feet,

184
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:22,461
and his clothes are
soaking wet, which means...

185
00:12:25,090 --> 00:12:28,430
What? He was drowned
somewhere else,

186
00:12:28,514 --> 00:12:30,727
then carried into this restroom?

187
00:12:30,810 --> 00:12:34,943
Yeah. Judging by the lividity
and the rigor mortis,

188
00:12:35,027 --> 00:12:38,200
he was probably killed
about an hour ago.

189
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:43,503
Right around when we were searching for him,
heading off to all those bars from here.

190
00:12:43,878 --> 00:12:46,926
And before we came
back here,

191
00:12:47,009 --> 00:12:50,349
the killer dumped the body in this
restroom and made their getaway.

192
00:12:50,432 --> 00:12:51,936
H-how could...

193
00:12:52,019 --> 00:12:53,898
Wh-who would do this...

194
00:12:54,858 --> 00:12:59,409
This guy was pretty well-built,
so it might be multiple culprits...

195
00:12:59,743 --> 00:13:03,668
or the work of someone
with serious physical strength.

196
00:13:04,545 --> 00:13:05,922
Um...
Hm?

197
00:13:06,005 --> 00:13:07,509
Hm?

198
00:13:09,847 --> 00:13:11,767
Did something happen?

199
00:13:15,775 --> 00:13:18,280
Right. The victim was

200
00:13:18,781 --> 00:13:23,499
Masahiro Tanba, age 32,
a middle school P.E. teacher.

201
00:13:24,417 --> 00:13:27,716
And the one who found the body
was a science teacher

202
00:13:27,799 --> 00:13:30,930
at the same middle school,
Sunami Masaki.

203
00:13:31,014 --> 00:13:33,393
Correct?
Yes.

204
00:13:34,061 --> 00:13:38,195
Now, could you tell me in detail
how you came to find the body?

205
00:13:38,529 --> 00:13:43,956
Y-yes. Today, Tanba-sensei,
my coworker Michiko here,

206
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:47,129
and I were supposed
to go bowling, the three of us.

207
00:13:47,714 --> 00:13:52,766
But on the way here, he got dead drunk
from the beers he'd had in the car

208
00:13:52,849 --> 00:13:55,145
and caused a scene in town,
which was a real handful,

209
00:13:55,229 --> 00:13:57,441
so we figured we'd let him
sleep it off until he sobered up

210
00:13:57,526 --> 00:13:59,655
and took him to Michiko's car.

211
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:03,704
Coworker, you said. So you're
a middle school teacher too?

212
00:14:03,788 --> 00:14:06,961
Oh, yes. I teach math.

213
00:14:07,044 --> 00:14:09,925
I see. And then?

214
00:14:10,008 --> 00:14:13,014
After bowling with Sunami
for about an hour,

215
00:14:13,098 --> 00:14:16,647
I went over to the car
to check on him.

216
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:20,446
He'd been through a lot,
so I couldn't leave him alone.

217
00:14:21,114 --> 00:14:26,332
But he wasn't in the car, so we all
panicked and went searching for him.

218
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:28,378
"We all," meaning?

219
00:14:28,462 --> 00:14:32,219
That would be the people we happened
to meet at the bowling alley...

220
00:14:32,303 --> 00:14:34,725
That's me,
Kogoro Mouri.

221
00:14:34,808 --> 00:14:37,939
Oh, well, if it isn't
Mouri-san.

222
00:14:38,023 --> 00:14:41,822
So we searched all over
the parking lot but couldn't find him.

223
00:14:41,906 --> 00:14:46,080
Thinking he might be off drinking again
at some bar somewhere,

224
00:14:46,164 --> 00:14:47,751
I split up with the girls

225
00:14:47,834 --> 00:14:51,299
and we spent about an hour
making the rounds of the local bars,

226
00:14:51,382 --> 00:14:55,307
but he was nowhere to be found,
so we came back to this lot.

227
00:14:55,934 --> 00:14:59,190
Figured he might have just
wandered back to the car.

228
00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:03,699
And sure enough, just as I thought,
he'd come back, all right.

229
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:09,001
As a cold drowned corpse
inside this parking lot's restroom.

230
00:15:09,085 --> 00:15:10,253
Dr-drowned?

231
00:15:10,797 --> 00:15:12,801
Is that true?
Yes.

232
00:15:12,884 --> 00:15:15,515
We can't say for certain
without an autopsy,

233
00:15:15,598 --> 00:15:18,938
but judging by the state of the body,
that's most likely the case.

234
00:15:19,564 --> 00:15:21,652
And the estimated
time of death?

235
00:15:21,735 --> 00:15:23,823
Around 5 p.m.

236
00:15:23,906 --> 00:15:26,829
I see. Around 5, you say.

237
00:15:27,162 --> 00:15:29,918
That's right around when we left
this parking lot for a while

238
00:15:30,002 --> 00:15:32,339
and started making the rounds
of the bars, right?

239
00:15:32,423 --> 00:15:33,592
Yeah.

240
00:15:33,676 --> 00:15:37,224
But when you first
came to search,

241
00:15:37,307 --> 00:15:39,353
why didn't you
check inside the restroom?

242
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:42,192
There was a padlock on it.

243
00:15:42,276 --> 00:15:45,867
And there was an "out of order"
notice posted on the door, too.

244
00:15:46,325 --> 00:15:48,246
A posted notice?

245
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:50,793
I saw it too.

246
00:15:50,877 --> 00:15:54,008
But the second time
we came to search here,

247
00:15:54,091 --> 00:15:58,726
that notice had been peeled off
and the padlock was gone,

248
00:15:58,809 --> 00:16:02,316
so... when I opened
the restroom door,

249
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:05,865
in-inside was
Tanba-sensei.

250
00:16:07,409 --> 00:16:12,419
So in other words, after the victim
was brought to the car by Sunami-san,

251
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:15,008
sometime before Michiko-san
came to check on him,

252
00:16:15,092 --> 00:16:16,804
he was abducted by someone,

253
00:16:16,887 --> 00:16:19,851
and while Mouri-san
and the others were touring the bars,

254
00:16:19,935 --> 00:16:21,897
he was drowned somewhere,

255
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:24,778
and then, before Mouri-san
and the others returned here,

256
00:16:24,861 --> 00:16:27,992
the body was placed
inside the restroom.

257
00:16:28,076 --> 00:16:30,080
Yeah. That's how it went.

258
00:16:30,665 --> 00:16:35,215
By the way, is there any chance
Tanba-san was being targeted by someone?

259
00:16:35,298 --> 00:16:41,770
Well... he turned into a different person
when he drank and picked fights with anyone,

260
00:16:41,854 --> 00:16:46,362
which is why he'd said he wasn't
going to drink a drop today.

261
00:16:46,446 --> 00:16:49,118
Hm.
Inspector Yamamura.

262
00:16:49,703 --> 00:16:51,999
There's a bruise
on the victim's abdomen.

263
00:16:52,082 --> 00:16:55,338
A bruise? You're right.

264
00:16:55,422 --> 00:16:57,760
Oh, that was probably me.

265
00:16:57,844 --> 00:16:59,221
Huh?

266
00:16:59,305 --> 00:17:02,269
He picked a fight while drunk
and took a swing at me,

267
00:17:02,352 --> 00:17:05,275
so reflexively, to the solar plexus.
A fight?

268
00:17:05,818 --> 00:17:08,824
He was shouting something
about how I'd made eye contact with him.

269
00:17:09,283 --> 00:17:12,331
Huh. That's awfully
good-natured of you.

270
00:17:12,414 --> 00:17:14,544
You were out searching for
that drunk too,

271
00:17:14,628 --> 00:17:16,297
along with Mouri-san
and the others, weren't you?

272
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:21,224
No. I was taking a nap inside
Mouri-san's car, which was parked here...

273
00:17:22,226 --> 00:17:23,479
Huh?

274
00:17:24,438 --> 00:17:27,361
I'm placing you under arrest
for murder.

275
00:17:27,737 --> 00:17:28,864
What?

276
00:17:28,948 --> 00:17:31,662
H-hey, hold on, Yamamura.

277
00:17:31,745 --> 00:17:34,834
Who kills someone just because
they got picked on?

278
00:17:34,918 --> 00:17:36,379
What are you trying to pull...

279
00:17:37,005 --> 00:17:39,343
What are you saying, Mouri-san?

280
00:17:39,426 --> 00:17:43,894
He just confessed, thanks to
my masterful interrogation technique.

281
00:17:44,228 --> 00:17:47,276
That he had a motive
and no alibi.

282
00:17:47,359 --> 00:17:51,910
B-but you can't make an arrest
on the spot over just that.

283
00:17:51,994 --> 00:17:54,791
Same as ever,
this bumbling fool.

284
00:17:56,795 --> 00:18:01,053
What are you talking about?
There's no way Makoto-san is the culprit.

285
00:18:01,137 --> 00:18:05,646
Hm? Then can you prove
his innocence?

286
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:08,151
Yes. I can.

287
00:18:08,527 --> 00:18:11,616
Because... because Makoto-san is...

288
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:13,328
Makoto-san is?

289
00:18:15,206 --> 00:18:21,177
Because he's such a wonderful,
kind, good person!

290
00:18:23,264 --> 00:18:25,435
(panting)

291
00:18:25,519 --> 00:18:27,690
That proves nothing.

292
00:18:28,191 --> 00:18:30,946
Inspector Yamamura, take a look at this.
Hm?

293
00:18:31,490 --> 00:18:34,203
There's a burn mark
on his left shoulder.

294
00:18:34,537 --> 00:18:38,545
The victim was likely
knocked out with a stun gun.

295
00:18:38,629 --> 00:18:39,714
A st-stun gun?

296
00:18:40,048 --> 00:18:42,595
If the killer used a stun gun,

297
00:18:42,678 --> 00:18:44,891
then I don't think
this guy's the culprit.

298
00:18:44,974 --> 00:18:46,478
Huh? Wh-why?

299
00:18:46,812 --> 00:18:51,613
Because a guy like him could knock
someone out with one punch to the gut,

300
00:18:51,696 --> 00:18:54,869
and since he'd already landed one,
hitting the same spot again

301
00:18:54,953 --> 00:18:56,873
would cover up the bruise.

302
00:18:56,957 --> 00:19:00,130
But maybe he used a stun gun
on purpose to make us think that.

303
00:19:00,756 --> 00:19:02,677
This karate master,

304
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:05,516
carrying a stun gun around
for self-defense?

305
00:19:05,599 --> 00:19:07,562
I really can't imagine it.

306
00:19:07,937 --> 00:19:09,899
A k-karate master?

307
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:13,239
He's won major tournaments
many times over.

308
00:19:13,322 --> 00:19:17,205
That's right. The undefeated
Prince of Kicks, 400 wins and no losses.

309
00:19:17,289 --> 00:19:20,003
Huh. Well, if that's the case,

310
00:19:20,086 --> 00:19:23,176
you should've said so... I mean,
please say so sooner.

311
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:24,804
Heh...

312
00:19:24,888 --> 00:19:27,685
We met during the
Red Handkerchief case, though.

313
00:19:28,311 --> 00:19:31,358
Yamamura, are you
feeling off or something?

314
00:19:31,442 --> 00:19:32,487
Huh?

315
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:35,868
You used to go around saying stuff like
"maybe you went and did it,

316
00:19:35,951 --> 00:19:37,747
or something like that,"
didn't you?

317
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:40,251
Th-that was just to
catch suspects off guard,

318
00:19:40,335 --> 00:19:42,214
I used it deliberately.

319
00:19:42,297 --> 00:19:45,554
Now that I've made inspector,
I have no need for

320
00:19:45,638 --> 00:19:49,646
such childish speech.
Nyah ha ha ha!

321
00:19:49,729 --> 00:19:51,148
Oh, is that so.

322
00:19:51,608 --> 00:19:54,071
So if you were here
in this lot the whole time,

323
00:19:54,154 --> 00:19:56,785
did you see anything?
Any suspicious people?

324
00:19:56,868 --> 00:19:59,666
No. I was fast asleep.

325
00:19:59,749 --> 00:20:02,087
I see. Fast asleep, huh.

326
00:20:02,547 --> 00:20:07,640
Whoa... h-hey,
hold on a second there!

327
00:20:10,896 --> 00:20:12,942
Phew. That was close.

328
00:20:13,234 --> 00:20:15,698
Isn't this area
tilted or something...

329
00:20:16,365 --> 00:20:20,958
Oh, this area's apparently sunk
a little due to ground subsidence.

330
00:20:21,626 --> 00:20:25,216
Seems they're planning to do
repair work next month, though.

331
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:26,469
Hmm.

332
00:20:27,012 --> 00:20:31,688
Ground subsidence...
Wait. If that's the case,

333
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:37,658
then these diagonal mud streaks
on the wall... could it be...

334
00:20:40,873 --> 00:20:43,879
Ah, rain.
Ugh, it's coming down again.

335
00:20:44,379 --> 00:20:47,052
For now, let's take shelter
in the bowling alley.

336
00:20:47,135 --> 00:20:49,181
We'll continue
the conversation there.

337
00:20:55,736 --> 00:20:56,738
Hm?

338
00:20:58,157 --> 00:21:01,831
What is it, Conan-kun?
You'd better hurry along too.

339
00:21:01,915 --> 00:21:03,209
Hey.
Hm?

340
00:21:03,627 --> 00:21:06,633
That spot on the restroom
vent... doesn't it look strange?

341
00:21:06,716 --> 00:21:08,553
Huh?
That one spot...

342
00:21:08,637 --> 00:21:12,102
the water droplets didn't run off,
they're left in a band.

343
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:16,611
It's a little sticky.

344
00:21:17,362 --> 00:21:19,116
Maybe something
was stuck on it.

345
00:21:20,744 --> 00:21:24,544
Hey, you two,
get inside quickly too.

346
00:21:24,627 --> 00:21:26,046
Okay.

347
00:21:32,016 --> 00:21:35,816
There are water droplets left
around the door the same way.

348
00:21:36,316 --> 00:21:39,281
It's like it was sealed up
with packing tape.

349
00:21:39,741 --> 00:21:43,372
But that guy didn't suffocate,
he drowned, right?

350
00:21:43,457 --> 00:21:45,209
Yeah.
And besides...

351
00:21:45,919 --> 00:21:49,719
there are no droplets left
on the vent at the bottom of the door.

352
00:21:50,303 --> 00:21:53,267
If it were sealed up,
that wouldn't make sense.

353
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:54,687
Right.

354
00:21:55,021 --> 00:21:58,612
And also, when we first
went into the restroom,

355
00:21:58,695 --> 00:22:00,908
didn't you smell it?
Yeah.

356
00:22:01,493 --> 00:22:04,372
The smell of kerosene.
You two.

357
00:22:05,041 --> 00:22:07,630
Weren't you listening
to what I just said?

358
00:22:07,713 --> 00:22:10,594
Yes, yes.
We're coming now.

359
00:22:10,677 --> 00:22:12,388
Heh heh heh.

360
00:22:32,178 --> 00:22:38,190
♪~

361
00:23:46,452 --> 00:23:51,754
~♪

362
00:23:52,380 --> 00:23:55,261
Hm? Sc-scorch marks
on the ceiling?

363
00:23:55,804 --> 00:23:58,810
Like I said, hurry up and make
the rounds of the bars around here

364
00:23:58,893 --> 00:24:00,897
and do a proper canvass.

365
00:24:01,273 --> 00:24:03,152
Oh, Makoto-san.
Ah.

366
00:24:03,235 --> 00:24:04,989
Leave him be.
Huh?

367
00:24:05,449 --> 00:24:09,498
Hey, kid. You help me
set up the trick.

368
00:24:10,291 --> 00:24:12,796
You've figured out this trick too, haven't you?

369
00:24:12,853 --> 00:24:18,253
Next Conan:
"Makoto Kyogoku, A Suspect? (Part 2)"

370
00:24:36,853 --> 00:24:39,153
Next Conan's Hint:

371
00:24:39,153 --> 00:24:41,153
"Witch"

372
00:24:41,383 --> 00:24:43,053
What's wrong, Ran-kun?
Staring at me like that.

373
00:24:43,136 --> 00:24:44,430
Karate vs. Jeet Kune Do...

374
00:24:44,514 --> 00:24:46,226
Has Ran-neechan
caught fire?
